<br>
#1 in total people killed - Chairman Mao<br>
<br>
#1 @#%$ of all time - hard to argue against Adolf Hitler<br>
<br>
#2 in the above categories - Stalin<br>
<br>
#1 in total % of own population killed - probably Pol Pot<br>
<br>
<br>
Genghis gets my vote though.  He changed the way the Mongols lived, reorganized them, borrowed the alphabet of their neighbors to give Mongols a written language, created the most dominating military the world would ever see.  From a group of squabbling nomads, he forged a powerful, cohesive empire.  What brought an end to Mongol dominance is of course the major weakness of any monarchy, no matter how well it starts, eventually somewhere down the bloodline things will break down.<br>
<br>
...and yes, Napoleon gets major consideration, but even he couldn't keep the French from losing in the end. <p>Ghune<br>
